      "text": "Fits a trend (linear, polynomial, exponential, or logarithmic) against a chosen x-column and subtracts it, leaving the residual (detrended) signal. Use it to remove baseline drift or sensor decay before rhythm analysis so a slow trend doesn't masquerade as a long period. An optional sliding window detrends locally. The demo shows the drifting input flattened around zero.",
